WHY PARASOL'S SMOKED PULLED PORK PO'BOY IS ONE OF NOLA'S BEST:

1.  SUCCULENTLY SMOKEY & MOIST, not charred and dry (e.g. a singed debris);
2.  CRUSTY BAGUETTE is more like a really good Banh Mí, not flimsy Leidenheimer;
3.  SPICY MAYNEZ SLAW: semi-sweet heat offsets the tartness of the cabbage;
4.  GRILLED ONIONS punctuate the flavors, & at a $1 extra are worth every penny;
5.  JUICY NOT MESSY: toasted egg washed crust retains much of the fragrant sauce;
6.  PRICE! It's huge! Feeds 2! $11!  With extra grilled onions just $12! Eat one a Day;
7.  YA HEARD?  Yat's spoken here & the counter kids are sweet locals, so TIP 'EM!

NON-SMOKERS: bypass the bar and go directly into the "smoke free" restaurant.  Enter through the first unmarked walk-up green door on Third Street.  This concept is similar to Milk Bar on Delachaise or Buffa's back room.
